 die Studie die philosophisch-kognitive Valenz der textuellen Darstellungsformen der Götzen-Dämmerung nach. Dabei werden insbesondere die Rolle von Selbstbezüglichkeitsfiguren sowie der von diesen häufig katalysierten ästhetischen oder intratextuellen Autosubversionen freigelegt.  aThis monograph examines the meaning and function of textuality and the aesthetic form of presentation in philosophy based on a close reading of selected passages from Nietzsche’s Twilight of the Idols. Drawing on philosophical and textual criticist theories, the study demonstrates the philosophical-cognitive valence of aesthetic forms of representation as well as the key role of self-referentiality in Nietzsche's philosophy.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 4aNietzsche, Friedrich. 4aphilosophisches Schreiben. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Language.2bisacsh  aPhilosophical writing, Nietzsche, Friedrich.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Philosophy 2000 - 2014z9783110636949oZDB-23-GPH08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Complete Package 2014z9783110369526oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2014z9783110370393oZDB-23-DPH0 cEPUBz97831103915960 cprintz978311036314240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311036423140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110364231423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110364231/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2014  aZDB-23-DPHb2014  aZDB-23-GPHc2000d2014